3. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with embedding a message in a cover-medium, which is a common problem in multimedia applications such as image and video steganography. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper discusses wet paper codes, which are used to improve the undetectability of the embedding by locking some components of the cover-data. This is a technique commonly used in image steganography, which falls under the domain of computer vision and pattern recognition.
